## Problem Statement

The 4 VSL pages have inconsistent:
- Color palettes (some pages use custom colors not in the brand system)
- Section structures (pages are missing pain points, results, or FAQ)
- Typography hierarchies
- CTA placement and copy
- Mobile layouts

This creates a fragmented experience that breaks the impression of being a "suite of services" from one trusted firm.

---

## Psychology Models Applied (PLFS)

| Model | PLFS | Application |
|---|---|---|
| **Authority Bias** | +13 | Badge + years experience + IRS credentials |
| **Loss Aversion** | +12 | Pain points ("Does this sound like you?") |
| **Social Proof** | +14 | Testimonials + stats + client logos |
| **Risk Reversal** | +11 | Guarantee + FAQ objection handling |
| **Paradox of Choice** | +12 | Single CTA focus, no nav distractions |

---

## Design System (Brand-Enforced)

All 4 VSL pages use **identical** brand tokens — industry differentiation comes from **content only**, never from colors.

```
Background:  bg-slate-950 (hero zone)  /  bg-white (content sections)
Primary:     brand-900 (#0F2339) — deep navy
Accent:      gold-500 (#D4A017) — gold highlights & CTAs
Text:        slate-900 (body) / white (on dark)
Success:     emerald-500 (results, checks)
Danger:      red-500 (urgency dot, announcement bar)
```

**Typography:**
- H1: `font-heading`, 4xl–6xl, bold, tight tracking
- H2: `font-heading`, 2xl–3xl, semibold
- Body: `font-sans` (Inter), base-lg, slate-600
- Numbers/Stats: `font-mono` or `font-heading`, 5xl–6xl, gold-500

---

## Unified Page Architecture (10 Sections)

All 4 VSL pages will share this exact section order:

| # | Section | Purpose | CTA? |
|---|---|---|---|
| 0 | **Announcement Bar** | Scarcity / urgency | — |
| 1 | **Hero** | Hook + video + primary CTA | ✅ Primary |
| 2 | **Trust Bar** | Proof numbers + logos | — |
| 3 | **Pain Points** | Agitation / identification | — |
| 4 | **How It Works** | 3-step process | — |
| 5 | **Results** | Specific metrics | ✅ Secondary |
| 6 | **Testimonial** | Featured social proof | — |
| 7 | **FAQ** | Objection handling | — |
| 8 | **Final CTA** | Conversion moment | ✅ Final |
| 9 | **Footer** | Trust + nav | — |

> **Mobile addition:** Sticky CTA bar at bottom of viewport (fixed position), visible at all scroll positions.

---

## Section-by-Section Specification

### Section 0: Announcement Bar
```
Height: 36px
Background: red-500
Content: "⚡ [Month] Partner Cohort — Only [N] Spots Available"
Text: white, sm, centered
Mobile: same, text slightly smaller
```

### Section 1: Hero
```
Background: radial gradient from brand-900 to slate-950
Layout: max-w-4xl centered, padding-x 6

Badge: small chip, gold-100 bg, gold-700 text, border gold-300
  → Industry-specific: "Construction Tax Partner" / "Restaurant CFO" etc.

H1: 4xl–6xl, white, bold, font-heading, 2–3 lines max
  → Pull from Sanity: heroHeadline

Subheadline: lg, slate-300, max-w-2xl centered
  → Pull from Sanity: heroSubheadline

Video: aspect-video, rounded-2xl, shadow-2xl, max-w-4xl
  → VideoEmbed component (existing)

CTA Row: two buttons
  → Primary: gold-500 bg, brand-900 text, "Book Free Strategy Call →"
  → Secondary: transparent, white border, white text, phone icon

Urgency: pulsing red dot + "Only [N] spots — [Month]"
```

### Section 2: Trust Bar
```
Background: white, border-b border-slate-100
Layout: flex, 5 stats spaced-evenly

Stat format: large number (gold-500) + label (slate-500, sm)
  → "$10M+ Resolved" / "500+ Clients" / "20+ Years" / "98% Success" / "IRS Certified"

Mobile: 2-column grid, 2+3 or 3+2 layout
```

### Section 3: Pain Points
```
Background: slate-50
Title: H2 "Does This Sound Like You?" centered

Items: 6 pain points (2-col grid desktop, 1-col mobile)
Each item:
  → Icon: alert-circle, red-500
  → Text: slate-700, font-medium
  → Subtle left border: red-200

Industry-specific content pulled from Sanity: painPoints[]
```

### Section 4: How It Works
```
Background: white
Title: H2 "Our Simple 3-Step Process"

3 cards horizontal (vertical stack mobile):
  → Number badge: brand-900 circle with white number
  → Icon: lucide icon, gold-500
  → Title: H3, bold, brand-900
  → Description: slate-600
  → Connector arrow between cards (desktop only)

Content from Sanity: howItWorks[] with title + description + icon
```

### Section 5: Results
```
Background: brand-900 (dark, for contrast)
Title: H2 white "Real Outcomes. Documented Results."

4-stat grid:
  → Large number: gold-500, 5xl, font-heading
  → Label: white/slate-300, sm

Secondary CTA below stats: outlined white button
Content from Sanity: results[] with stat + label
```

### Section 6: Testimonial
```
Background: white
Layout: max-w-3xl centered

Featured card:
  → 5 gold stars
  → Large blockquote: xl, slate-700, italic
  → Avatar + Name + Company + Industry badge
  → Optional: before/after metric (e.g. "Saved $47k in 6 months")

Content from Sanity: testimonial object
```

### Section 7: FAQ
```
Background: slate-50
Title: H2 "Frequently Asked Questions"

3 accordion items, industry-specific objections:
  - "How much does this cost?"
  - "How long does the process take?"
  - "What if I have unpaid taxes/penalties?"

Content from Sanity: faqs[] with question + answer
```

### Section 8: Final CTA
```
Background: gradient brand-900 → brand-800

H2: white, "Ready to Stop Struggling With [Industry Problem]?"
Sub: gold-300 text, specific outcome promise  
CTA Button: gold-500, large, full-width on mobile
  → "Book Your Free [Industry] Strategy Call →"
Trust signals: "Free. No obligation. 15-minute call."
```

### Mobile Sticky CTA Bar
```
Position: fixed bottom-0, full-width, z-50
Background: brand-900
Content: Phone icon + "Book Free Call" gold button
Visible: all times on mobile (hidden on desktop)
Padding: safe-area-inset for iOS
```

---

## Component Strategy

### New: `UnifiedVSLTemplate.tsx`
A shared wrapper component that all 4 VSL pages will use:

```tsx
// Usage pattern
<UnifiedVSLTemplate data={sanitizedData} industry="construction" />
```

**Props interface:**
```tsx
interface VSLTemplateData {
  badge: string;
  heroHeadline: string;
  heroSubheadline: string;
  heroCtaText: string;
  heroCtaUrl: string;
  videoUrl: string;
  trustStats: { value: string; label: string }[];
  painPoints: { text: string }[];
  howItWorks: { title: string; description: string; icon: string }[];
  results: { value: string; label: string }[];
  testimonial: { quote: string; name: string; company: string; rating: number };
  faqs: { question: string; answer: string }[];
  finalCtaHeadline: string;
  finalCtaSubtext: string;
  announcementText: string;
}
```

### Existing Components Retained
- [VideoEmbed](file:///Volumes/MiDRIVE/WORK/U-Z/UNION%20NATIONAL%20TAX/unionnational/src/components/ui/VideoEmbed.tsx#14-108) — unchanged
- [FloatingNavbar](file:///Volumes/MiDRIVE/WORK/U-Z/UNION%20NATIONAL%20TAX/unionnational/src/components/layout/FloatingNavbar.tsx#40-52) (via VSL layout) — unchanged
- `Footer` (via VSL layout) — unchanged
- `LuxuryTravelIncentive` — optional, placed in Final CTA section

