## Verification Plan

### Automated
- `npm run build` — no TypeScript errors
- `npm run dev` — all 4 VSL pages render without crashes

### Manual Visual Checks
- [ ] All 4 pages render the same section order
- [ ] Brand colors (gold-500, brand-900) consistent across all pages
- [ ] Videos play on all pages
- [ ] Navbar and footer present on all pages
- [ ] Mobile sticky CTA bar appears below 768px
- [ ] Announcement bar renders on all pages
- [ ] Testimonial section visible (previously missing on some pages)
- [ ] FAQ section operational

### Responsive Checks
- [ ] Desktop (1440px) — 10 sections render side-by-side where appropriate
- [ ] Tablet (768px) — grid collapses to 2-col
- [ ] Mobile (390px) — full single-column, sticky bar visible

---

## Implementation Order

1. Create `UnifiedVSLTemplate.tsx` with all sub-sections
2. Create all `VSL*.tsx` sub-components
3. Update Sanity schemas with new fields
4. Refactor all 4 `*Client.tsx` files to use template
5. Verify all pages in dev server
6. Write walkthrough
